data.text:
Ubon Ratchathani, Thailand

ฺBelow a scenic cliff of Pha Taem National Park, out in the far northeast region of Thailand, the Sang Chan Waterfall is a natural wonder that attracts countless visitors. Here the water flows trough a natural hole the massaive overhanging rock, and when moon is full the moonlight streams through the hole and illuminates the water as it flows. Couples hoping to catch this spectacle can pitch a tent in the park campsite, or rent a romantic bungalow or cabin, and then the next day go explore the flower gardens, prehistoric cave paiting or one of the other spectacular waterfalls the park has to offer.
